## 🛡️ Security & Best Practices

### ALWAYS include:

- Input validation (ai/guides/04-SKILLS_API.md)
- Error handling (ai/guides/04-SKILLS_API.md)
- Rate limiting (ai/guides/02-DEBUGGING.md Issue #3)
- Webhook verification (ai/agents/security.agent.md)

### NEVER:

- Log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, card numbers)
- Trust unverified webhooks
- Use hardcoded secrets
- Skip input validation
- Assume data types

### ALWAYS verify:

- JWT token in HTTP-only cookie
- CORS origin is whitelisted
- Database queries use .lean() for reads
- N+1 queries are fixed
- Indexes exist on queried fields

---

## 📊 Performance Standards

### API Response Time

- Target: < 500ms (P95)
- Use `.lean()` for read-only queries
- Paginate large datasets
- Add database indexes

### Database Optimization

- Use `.select()` to exclude unused fields
- Check for N+1 queries
- Use aggregation for complex queries
- Monitor connection pooling

### Memory Management

- Stream large datasets
- Don't load entire collections
- Use pagination for lists
- Clean up Redis keys

